                      Tales from Italy                    The Consul General of Italy in Calcutta, in collaboration with Nandan West Bengal Film Centre and Roopkala Kendra, is screening a package of Italian films (with English sub-titles). To be screened today are Callas Forever (dir: Franco Zeffirelli, 4 pm) and Cera una Volta il West (Once Upon A Time in the West; dir: Sergio Leone, 6.30 pm). The former film (a still from it appears above) is a fictionalised account of the last days of opera singer Maria Callas. The latter is the epic story of a mysterious stranger with a harmonica who joins forces with a notorious desperado to protect a beautiful widow from a ruthless assassin working for the railroad.                  Event: Screening of Italian films When: Till April 3; 4 pm amp; 6.30 pm Where: Nandan II	                    
